 reform emerged at the interstices of local Iranian and Western-dominated global contexts and concerns.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aScience and civilization. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  a1900.  a1950.  a20th century.  abiomedical sciences.  acivic.  aclass differences.  aclass.  ademographics.  aeconomic power.  aeveryday life.  aglobal concerns.  aglobal contexts.  ahistorical.  airanian culture.  airanian modernists.  airanian society.  amiddle class.  amiddle east.  amodern history.  amodern iran.  amodern problems.  amodern science.  amodern stresses.  anonfiction.  arevolution.  ascience.  ascientific knowledge.  asocial distinctions.  asocial reform.  awestern context.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025447340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094354440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943544423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943544/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY